title: For Sale/Trade:  **SOLD PENDING TRANSACTION** BARELY Used S&W Bodyguard .38 Spl +P revolver **SOLD PENDING TRANSACTION**
postcontent:
S&W Bodyguard .38 Spl +P DAO revolver 5 shot, 1 7/8" barrel.  Comes equipped with built in Insight laser that I sighted in with the tools provided as best I could for the small amount of ammo that this gun has fired (30 rds).  Seems to be pretty spot on though at 7 yds at least.

I bought this gun a month ago at Targetmaster in Chadds Ford for my girlfriend brand new I paid $469.99 plus taxes.  It has been to the range once before where we put 30 rounds downrange before she decided the recoil was too much for her to handle (we were shooting +P rounds so that didn't help with recoil on a lightweight snubby as you might imagine, I had a ton of fun shooting this gun though, functions flawlessly).  Anyway, I bought an aftermarket Hogue Tamer grip (was about $22, this is what is equipped now and in all of the pictures).  I haven't shot it since but it feels SO much better equipped to fire hot rounds now.  It feels like follow up shots will be incredibly easier than they were with the tiny original grip and from what I've read greatly improves accuracy though I can't vouch for that myself.  So we were going to pick up some standard pressure .38 Spl rounds and head to the range to try it out with the new grip and lighter rounds when she informed me that she didn't like revolvers and wanted a small semi auto instead.  Wish I knew this before I bought it but hey it happens.  So after handling a bunch of semi's she's set on the Ruger LC9.

Price includes everything that came new with the gun (Cardboard box, Soft case that zips up with sewn in holster and loop to hold a speed loader (looks like a CD/DVD case you could walk around with it and nobody would think twice), User Manual, lock, tools to adjust the laser, etc. the usual stuff).  Only thing with it that it does not have is the spent shell casing from the factory since the instructions that came with the Hogue Tamer grip said to use a spent .38 casing to pry the bottom of the grip onto the pin and that was the only one I had which dented the casing to all hell (the grip is tough), but it has the signed envelope.  Also included is the original grip with the roll pin to attach it (You may want to pick up a new roll pin if you reinstall the original grip but I have no idea why anyone would want to go back to the original very hard rubber grip but it's there anyway), an Uncle Mike's IWB Concealed Carry holster, 23 rounds of .38 Spl +P Remington 125 gr SJHP's and a box of Buffalo Bore standard pressure short barrel low flash heavy 38 Spl 125 gr JHP's (Non +P but they're Buffalo Bore and advertise at 900 fps muzzle velocity and designed to expand at much lower than that, they're designed for snubbies).  Saving my cheap FMJ's to fire out of my GP-100 .357 Mag.  

Overall, this is an awesome gun and if I didn't already have an XDs .45 for a CCW, I'd happily keep it for myself.  I hate to get rid of it after using it so little but I promised her a gun and can't afford to keep it while buying an LC9 and I also need to save up for a Glock 20 for myself so I really have no choice but to sell/trade it.

Email me with any questions, concerns, offers.  I'm open to all offers worst I can say is no.  Will only meet FTF at an FFL within a reasonable distance (Targetmaster, French Creek, Double Action, etc)  I will not ship it anywhere.  Buyer also pays the transfer fee to the FFL.  Thanks for looking.  Asking $450 for everything.  I'll take $425 if you don't want the ammo.  I've put about $575 total into all this and it's basically brand new.  I have all of the paperwork for it.

title: For Sale:  Para Ordnance 7.45 LDA
location: Sumter, SC, South Carolina, United States
postcontent:
The LDA refers to the 7.45's light double action trigger, a feature that differentiates it from stiff, hard to use double-action-only pistols. The LDA trigger has a long arc of movement with a relatively low level of resistance to pressure from the shooter's finger both through the stroke and, most critically, at the point of release. And the 7.45 still features the thumb safety and grip safety of the original 1911A1, making it easy to secure against unintended discharges, and fast into action from the holster. The incredibly accurate fully ramped, match-type barrel is also crowned and forged, something normally seen only on a custom 1911. The gun is very smoothly finished and its sight has deep lateral serrations to cut down glare. This pistol features 3-white-dot sights, wooden grips and a 7-round magazine.

Includes box, holster, magazine holster, and 3 factory magazines.

postcontent:
Hey everyone, 
I have up for sale a 2001 Nissan Xterra. It is the powerful 6-cylinder engine and is 4x4. This is the automatic transmission. This also has power windows and locks. The tires on it are decent and the 4x4 works great (as the recent snowstorms have shown us!). This has keyless entry and rear wiper. This shows 123K miles and it still runs fine. This has two keys and two keyless entry remotes. This is a fantastic truck and would be great for anyone needing a reliable car. The A/C blows cold and the heater blows hot! It has the sunroof and the rack insert that covers the glass up when not in use (the thing everyone breaks or loses). This also comes with a Haynes repair manual that lists out everything I have done to the vehicle for the time that we have owned it. This also has the trailer hitch installed as well. Here is a brief list of what has been done to it recently 
-Fresh oil and filter change 
-Brand new front Windshield 
-Spectre Performance Air Filter 
-New Headlight Bulbs 
-Aftermarket Grille guard (Light ready!) 
-New SSL 6.5 door speakers 
-New 6x9 rear speakers 
-Brand New Radiator and Flushed Coolant System! 

If you have any questions please shoot me an email on here, or shoot me a text only to REDACTED and I will respond ASAP. For any specifics or any questions don't hesitate to message me! This is a used vehicle so please don't expect it to be perfect; she has her dings and a few fluid leaks, but nothing that would make it "ugly". We would be asking a significant amount more if I had the time to fix the leak and the light was off, I just dont have time and we need it gone.It appears to have a valve cover gasket leak causing a decent oil spot under the truck. I have already bought the gaskets and grommets (will come with the truck at no extra cost) I just don't have the time to put it on yet due to school, work, and my internship. It is minor enough of a leak that I have been driving it this whole time with no other problems or noticeable issues, i just monitor the fluid level. Just like most other Xterras out there the check engine light occasionally pops on (it's on as of now). We've taken it into the shop a couple times and every time they tell us that it is nothing major and that it wont effect anything mechanical. (usually like a loose connector issue or occasionally the O2 or cat sensor) Either way, it has been this way since we bought it about a year ago and it has never given us any kind of issue with it. Also, if you let the truck sit for a few days and do not start it the battery seems weak. but with regular driving it seems fine. Even if it needed replaced it is a comparatively cheap fix. Plus, we have it priced very fair considering taking into account the relatively low costs of the probable repairs. This drove perfect through the snow like nothing was out of the ordinary! This has an up to date tag and clear title ready to become yours! Spend your tax return on something that will last! This is obviously "as is" "where is" so feel free to ask any and all questions and I will answer them ASAP! Really not looking for any trades but would consider "partial" trades for firearm related items. But we are mainly just looking for cash.

title: For Sale:  Ultrasonic Gun Cleaning
postcontent:
Perfect for an old gun that needs a good deep cleaning, a gun with a lot of rust, a heavy used gun, hunting rifles, 22's, and pretty much any other gun that is dirty.

This includes disassembling the gun completely, removing any rust, soaking every part in a heavy degreaser, and scrubbing the gun entirely. After, it is soaked in the degreaser again. Then, all parts are polished by hand, then are put in the ultrasonic bath to remove any lingering polishing compounds, and then all of the parts are put in pressure soak with a deep penetrating lubricant to ensure that the lubricant gets into the pores of the metal, and doesn't just coat it.

This process keeps your gun running smoother, and more accurate for way longer than the typical "basic" clean that people do to their firearms.

All of my work is ensured by 100% cash payment, no questions asked. If anything gets damaged, which it never has, I will pay for the gun in full.

The MCU-2/P gas mask is an authentic piece of United States Military history. This USGI mask was originally adopted in the early 1990s and was used by both the U.S. Navy and the U.S. Air Force. The mask was used during the Gulf War after replacing the M17 gas mask, but was later replaced by the current-issue M50 Joint Service general purpose mask. Though it is no longer in production, these gas masks are still very much sought after for numerous reasons, including their comfort, tight seal, wide lens and protective capabilities.

MSA’s MCU-2/P is easily one of our best gas masks. To start out, the gas mask is fully adjustable with the inclusion of a six-point adjustable harness. The harness features zip-pulls for a quick and proper fitting. Also noteworthy is the wide ballistic polycarbonate lens that provides a panoramic view, virtually eliminating the visual problems associated with lesser masks. The exhalation valve makes breathing a breeze and the use of a front-mounted voice emitter makes speech both audible and clear. The MCU-2/P gas mask accepts standard NATO 40mm filters. The addition of dual filter ports makes the use of a rifle in conjunction with the mask very simple. A filter can be installed on either side of the face, providing a clear field of vision while shooting.

As noted, the MCU-2/P gas mask provides proven protection. This mask has been used in combat and is now ready to serve you as well.
